00:05:06.010 --> 00:05:09.170
So the first thing we
did is we started looking

00:05:09.170 --> 00:05:11.450
at all the refunded orders.

00:05:11.450 --> 00:05:15.350
So these are orders that
either we gave a refund for

00:05:15.350 --> 00:05:18.350
or that the bank has
given a chargeback on.

00:05:18.350 --> 00:05:20.090
And we were trying
to think about

00:05:20.090 --> 00:05:23.270
how can we get our developers
to know about these orders

00:05:23.270 --> 00:05:28.910
so you can actually take that
physical vacuum cleaner back.

00:05:28.910 --> 00:05:32.574
So what we did is we--
actually, let me just

00:05:32.574 --> 00:05:33.740
walk you through an example.

00:05:33.740 --> 00:05:36.980
So what we did is we looked
at all the refunded orders.

00:05:36.980 --> 00:05:41.390
A user comes into Google Play,
maybe made a $10 purchase

00:05:41.390 --> 00:05:43.670
for 10,000 coins.

00:05:43.670 --> 00:05:46.190
If we approve a refund
there, what we do now

00:05:46.190 --> 00:05:49.310
is we store those orders
in a voided order table.

00:05:49.310 --> 00:05:53.810
So these orders are labeled as
in do not deliver or claw back.

00:05:53.810 --> 00:05:55.860
With the API, what you
can do as a developer--

00:05:55.860 --> 00:05:57.290
you can call this API.

00:05:57.290 --> 00:05:59.780
It's called the
Voided Purchases API.

00:05:59.780 --> 00:06:02.150
You can receive the
data on that order,

00:06:02.150 --> 00:06:04.430
and you can then
claw back the item.

00:06:04.430 --> 00:06:06.920
So what happens is the user
gets their refund approved.

00:06:06.920 --> 00:06:09.020
They get their $10.

00:06:09.020 --> 00:06:12.290
But once you call that API
and you have that order,

00:06:12.290 --> 00:06:14.720
you can take the
10,000 gems back.

00:06:14.720 --> 00:06:17.120
So we learned that this
works really, really

00:06:17.120 --> 00:06:18.050
well for refunds.

00:06:18.050 --> 00:06:21.500
And I have a next
slide on impact.

00:06:21.500 --> 00:06:24.120
So we extended it to other
types of orders as well.

00:06:24.120 --> 00:06:25.630
We looked at cancellations.

00:06:25.630 --> 00:06:29.620
We looked at banks or issuers
giving chargebacks out,

00:06:29.620 --> 00:06:32.090
and we added those as well.

00:06:32.090 --> 00:06:34.940
And this works really, really,
really well for bad users.

00:06:34.940 --> 00:06:36.950
It also works well
for good users.

00:06:36.950 --> 00:06:39.130
Because we believe
that as a good user,

00:06:39.130 --> 00:06:41.090
you're OK getting
back to your money

00:06:41.090 --> 00:06:44.970
and willing to give up the coins
that you purchased with it.

00:06:44.970 --> 00:06:46.280
So here's the impact slide.

00:06:46.280 --> 00:06:48.770
We've been piloting this
for about 10 to 12 months

00:06:48.770 --> 00:06:50.450
with a couple of
different developers.

00:06:50.450 --> 00:06:53.210
We've seen really, really
big impact everywhere.

00:06:53.210 --> 00:06:57.130
So on average, we see refunds
decrease with more than 60%

00:06:57.130 --> 00:07:00.620
in about two to
three months' time.

00:07:00.620 --> 00:07:03.060
So what happens is it takes
time for the community,

00:07:03.060 --> 00:07:05.480
and especially for
abusers, to find out

00:07:05.480 --> 00:07:09.150
that this abuse factor is gone.

00:07:09.150 --> 00:07:11.662
So now we get into a
little bit more details.

00:07:11.662 --> 00:07:13.120
Because of course,
you want to know

00:07:13.120 --> 00:07:14.930
how can I do this for my game.

00:07:14.930 --> 00:07:16.820
So this is an Early Access API.

00:07:16.820 --> 00:07:19.730
So you have to sign up, and
we'll show you a link later on.

00:07:19.730 --> 00:07:21.830
And we'll also send you
the detailed documentation

00:07:21.830 --> 00:07:23.621
so you don't have to
take pictures of this.

00:07:23.621 --> 00:07:27.320
But broadly, how it
works is you give us

00:07:27.320 --> 00:07:29.750
the start time and the
end time of a time period

00:07:29.750 --> 00:07:32.000
for which you want to have
all the voided purchases.

00:07:32.000 --> 00:07:33.740
You call our API.

00:07:33.740 --> 00:07:37.850
We give you back a list of
orders keyed by purchase token.

00:07:37.850 --> 00:07:39.830
And then what you can
do with that is you

00:07:39.830 --> 00:07:44.570
can use that to revoke
access to those orders.

00:07:44.570 --> 00:07:47.000
Let me talk to you a
little bit about the three

00:07:47.000 --> 00:07:52.100
different approaches that we've
seen developers use our data.

00:07:52.100 --> 00:07:54.880
I'll go from really, really
simple to more complicated.

00:07:54.880 --> 00:07:57.710
So the simplest way is
user purchases something

00:07:57.710 --> 00:08:01.070
like 10,000 coins for $10.

00:08:01.070 --> 00:08:03.800
We send you the voided
order, and what happens

00:08:03.800 --> 00:08:06.880
is you claw back
exactly those 10,000

00:08:06.880 --> 00:08:08.600
gems from the user's balance.

00:08:08.600 --> 00:08:10.440
So the user is now--
their current balance

00:08:10.440 --> 00:08:11.930
is minus 10,000.

00:08:11.930 --> 00:08:15.020
But of course, there's many,
many games where you don't only

00:08:15.020 --> 00:08:17.470
get 10,000 gems, but
you get 10,000 gems

00:08:17.470 --> 00:08:21.310
plus one or two or maybe
three special characters.

00:08:21.310 --> 00:08:23.060
So that's the second
case that we've seen,

00:08:23.060 --> 00:08:27.440
is where developers say we don't
only claw back the 10,000 gems,

00:08:27.440 --> 00:08:29.450
but also, we take
anything that we

00:08:29.450 --> 00:08:32.780
added on to that-- some special
powers, special characters,

00:08:32.780 --> 00:08:35.380
and we claw that back as well.

00:08:35.380 --> 00:08:38.480
The third case that we've seen--
I guess the most complicated

00:08:38.480 --> 00:08:41.450
case-- is where
you take snapshots

00:08:41.450 --> 00:08:44.560
at the user state at
the moment of purchase.

00:08:44.560 --> 00:08:47.360
So say this user bought
these 10,000 gems,

00:08:47.360 --> 00:08:50.000
say, two weeks ago,
and with those 10,000

00:08:50.000 --> 00:08:52.850
gems was able to get
two special characters

00:08:52.850 --> 00:08:54.560
and go up three levels.

00:08:54.560 --> 00:08:56.410
What we've seen
is developers who,

00:08:56.410 --> 00:08:58.420
m when they get
the refunded order,

00:08:58.420 --> 00:09:00.950
take the user back two weeks.

00:09:00.950 --> 00:09:03.527
And then the user is
actually back three levels,

00:09:03.527 --> 00:09:05.360
loses their two to three
special characters,

00:09:05.360 --> 00:09:07.510
and loses the 10,000 gems.

00:09:07.510 --> 00:09:09.800
So this worked really
well in stopping abuse.

00:09:09.800 --> 00:09:12.290
And we also really believe
that this works really, really

00:09:12.290 --> 00:09:14.250
well for good users.

